1
00:00:26,738 --> 00:00:29,673
My mother died of pneumonia
when I was just a kid.

2
00:00:29,741 --> 00:00:33,677
My father had kept their wedding cake
in the freezer for ten whole years.

3
00:00:33,745 --> 00:00:36,680
After the funeral he gave it
to the yard man.

4
00:00:36,848 --> 00:00:39,612
He tried to act cheerful,
but he could never be consoled...

5
00:00:39,685 --> 00:00:42,415
...by the little stranger
he found in his house.

6
00:00:42,554 --> 00:00:47,457
Then, one day, hoping to begin a new life
away from the scene offal his memories...

7
00:00:47,926 --> 00:00:51,327
...he moved us from Texas
to Fort Dupree, South Dakota.

8
00:01:34,172 --> 00:01:36,606
I'll give you a dollar to eat this Collie.

9
00:01:42,814 --> 00:01:44,839
I ain't gonna eat him for a dollar.

10
00:01:46,885 --> 00:01:48,910
I don't think he's a Collie either.

11
00:01:49,121 --> 00:01:50,782
Some kind of dog, though.

12
00:01:52,758 --> 00:01:53,850
Watch your head.

13
00:02:00,232 --> 00:02:01,324
Hey, Woody!

14
00:02:02,134 --> 00:02:03,499
Give me a cigarette!

15
00:02:07,472 --> 00:02:09,440
Woody wouldn't give me a cigarette.

16
00:02:11,743 --> 00:02:13,802
Ever notice he don't talk much?

17
00:02:14,046 --> 00:02:16,913
Yeah, he's not a talker. You got that.

18
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:23,517
Little did I realize, what began in the alleys
and back ways of this quiet town...

19
00:02:23,822 --> 00:02:26,655
...would end in the Badlands of Montana.

20
00:02:28,593 --> 00:02:30,823
-No, they wouldn't fit.
-You haven't tried 'em on.

21
00:02:30,896 --> 00:02:33,228
-No, no. What size are they?
-Your size.

22
00:02:33,598 --> 00:02:35,623
-Come on, give me a dollar for 'em.
-No.

23
00:02:35,767 --> 00:02:37,564
They cost $20 new.

24
00:02:40,906 --> 00:02:42,999
Why don't you see if they fit you?

25
00:02:55,887 --> 00:02:58,219
This lady don't ever pay her bills.

26
00:03:00,358 --> 00:03:03,088
She's gonna get in trouble
if she doesn't watch out.

27
00:03:12,971 --> 00:03:16,463
I throwed enough trash for today, Cato.
I'll see you in the morning.

28
00:03:18,777 --> 00:03:19,766
Catch!

29
00:03:20,579 --> 00:03:22,012
What do you mean?

30
00:04:19,171 --> 00:04:20,160
Hi.

31
00:04:20,505 --> 00:04:21,836
I'm Kit.

32
00:04:21,907 --> 00:04:24,398
I'm not keepin' you
from anything important, am l?

33
00:04:24,476 --> 00:04:25,135
No.

34
00:04:25,911 --> 00:04:28,539
Just thought I'd come over
and say hello to you.

35
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,479
I'll try anything once.

36
00:04:34,452 --> 00:04:36,113
What's your name? I said mine.

37
00:04:36,521 --> 00:04:37,351
Holly.

38
00:04:39,057 --> 00:04:40,718
Well listen, Holly....

39
00:04:41,359 --> 00:04:44,851
You, I don't know....
You want to take a walk with me?

40
00:04:46,231 --> 00:04:47,391
What for?

41
00:04:47,999 --> 00:04:49,660
I got some stuff to say.

42
00:04:50,101 --> 00:04:52,069
Guess I'm kind of lucky that way.

43
00:04:52,137 --> 00:04:54,867
Most people don't have anything
on their minds, do they?

44
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:02,004
Incidentally, my last name is Carruthers.

45
00:05:03,215 --> 00:05:05,547
Sounds a little too much like "druthers."

46
00:05:05,617 --> 00:05:06,914
It's okay.

47
00:05:07,485 --> 00:05:10,283
Yeah, well nobody asked me
what I thought.

48
00:05:10,422 --> 00:05:12,185
They just hung it on me.

49
00:05:14,893 --> 00:05:16,656
You still in school?

50
00:05:17,095 --> 00:05:18,892
No, I got me a job.

51
00:05:19,564 --> 00:05:20,929
Doin' what?

52
00:05:21,499 --> 00:05:25,731
Well, I don't mind gettin' up early
so I got a job throwing garbage.

53
00:05:27,105 --> 00:05:28,037
Holly!

54
00:05:28,106 --> 00:05:30,006
I'm not in love with the stuff, okay?

55
00:05:30,075 --> 00:05:31,975
That's my father. I gotta run.

56
00:05:32,043 --> 00:05:33,203
Hey, wait!

57
00:05:33,311 --> 00:05:34,903
When am I gonna see you again?

58
00:05:37,449 --> 00:05:39,644
Well, I know what my daddy's gonna say.

59
00:05:39,718 --> 00:05:40,707
What?

60
00:05:40,785 --> 00:05:41,877
Can I be honest?

61
00:05:42,387 --> 00:05:43,376
Sure.

62
00:05:44,789 --> 00:05:48,589
Well, that I shouldn't be seen
with anybody that collects garbage.

63
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:49,888
He'll say that?

64
00:05:50,795 --> 00:05:51,625
Yeah.

65
00:05:52,297 --> 00:05:54,094
Now what's he know about garbage?

66
00:05:54,766 --> 00:05:55,733
Nothin'.

67
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,233
There you go.

68
00:05:57,636 --> 00:06:01,299
I mean, there's nothin' he wants to know.
I gotta run.

69
00:06:09,481 --> 00:06:10,880
Who was that?

70
00:06:11,049 --> 00:06:12,448
Just some boy.

71
00:06:14,286 --> 00:06:16,220
Is that gonna kill the grass?

72
00:06:18,723 --> 00:06:20,623
You got some on my feet!

73
00:06:21,927 --> 00:06:23,417
What'd he want?

74
00:06:23,561 --> 00:06:26,086
He was just askin' if we needed
any yard work done.

75
00:06:29,401 --> 00:06:32,427
I said, "No." And for him not to bother us.

76
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:40,539
Heard the news, Kit?

77
00:06:41,913 --> 00:06:42,709
No.

78
00:06:43,581 --> 00:06:45,048
Been in all the headlines.

79
00:06:46,818 --> 00:06:47,807
What's that?

80
00:06:47,886 --> 00:06:49,217
You've been fired.

81
00:06:49,721 --> 00:06:51,450
Ain't that a hell of a note?

82
00:06:54,459 --> 00:06:56,188
Yeah, how about that?

83
00:06:57,262 --> 00:07:00,026
I wouldn't be needin' my keys anymore.

84
00:07:00,098 --> 00:07:02,623
I'll just leave 'em
where they'll be nice and handy.

85
00:07:06,938 --> 00:07:08,235
I've got my dog.

86
00:07:10,241 --> 00:07:12,232
Have you ever held another job before?

87
00:07:13,545 --> 00:07:16,480
Yeah, I used to throw trash for the city.

88
00:07:17,649 --> 00:07:19,514
And you lost that one?

89
00:07:19,918 --> 00:07:22,648
Yeah, I wouldn't be here if I hadn't.

90
00:07:24,022 --> 00:07:25,421
Why did you leave?

91
00:07:27,025 --> 00:07:28,117
Just felt like it.

92
00:07:29,627 --> 00:07:32,528
What kind of work do you think
you'd be qualified for?

93
00:07:32,597 --> 00:07:34,360
I just gotta get this.

94
00:07:39,504 --> 00:07:42,632
Well, I can't think of anything
at the moment.

95
00:07:45,543 --> 00:07:49,843
I want you to write me out a slip though,
provin' I came down here.

96
00:07:52,884 --> 00:07:56,047
I think we can get you something.
Workin' cattle over at the pens.

97
00:08:01,026 --> 00:08:02,653
Yeah, what the hell.

98
00:08:03,628 --> 00:08:05,619
Just hope there's a breeze.

99
00:08:14,072 --> 00:08:16,734
He was handsomer
than anybody I'd ever met.

100
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:19,173
He looked just like James Dean.

101
00:08:21,146 --> 00:08:22,135
Hi.

102
00:08:22,347 --> 00:08:24,076
Well, stop the world.

103
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,512
Hey, quit my job.

104
00:08:26,584 --> 00:08:27,573
Great.

105
00:08:28,319 --> 00:08:31,049
Seemed like the right move.
What'cha doing?

106
00:08:31,222 --> 00:08:32,246
Spanish.

107
00:08:33,058 --> 00:08:35,754
How do you say:
"Quit my job," in Spanish?

108
00:08:36,261 --> 00:08:38,092
Something...mi trabajo.

109
00:08:39,230 --> 00:08:41,323
Well, I'm goin' to work as a cowboy now.

110
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,958
Thinkin' about it.

111
00:08:46,504 --> 00:08:48,438
It's a routine like anything.

112
00:08:49,774 --> 00:08:51,105
What do you think?

113
00:08:51,543 --> 00:08:52,567
I don't know.

114
00:08:53,611 --> 00:08:57,707
Yeah, well, at least nobody can get on me
about wearin' these boots anymore.

115
00:09:05,123 --> 00:09:07,057
You want to go for a ride?

116
00:09:10,395 --> 00:09:12,056
Well, I got homework.

117
00:09:14,065 --> 00:09:15,555
Bring it along.

118
00:09:20,338 --> 00:09:22,738
Somebody dropped a bag on the sidewalk.

119
00:09:26,010 --> 00:09:28,843
If everybody did that,
the whole town'd be a mess.

120
00:09:33,218 --> 00:09:34,207
Hi.

121
00:09:36,554 --> 00:09:37,987
You're a redhead.

122
00:09:38,056 --> 00:09:39,114
I know.

123
00:09:40,525 --> 00:09:42,425
Anybody ever call you "Red"?

124
00:09:42,660 --> 00:09:44,059
Yeah, but I don't like it.

125
00:09:44,129 --> 00:09:45,118
Why not?

126
00:09:46,331 --> 00:09:47,730
I just don't.

127
00:09:50,502 --> 00:09:51,662
I got a headache.

128
00:09:51,736 --> 00:09:52,964
Oh, yeah?

129
00:10:03,715 --> 00:10:05,740
Can I come around and see you tomorrow?

130
00:10:05,817 --> 00:10:06,841
Okay.

131
00:10:18,596 --> 00:10:22,362
Kit went to work in the feedlot
while I carried on with my studies.

132
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:24,526
Little by little, we fell in love.

133
00:10:24,903 --> 00:10:28,999
As I'd never been popular in school,
and didn't have a lot of personality...

134
00:10:29,073 --> 00:10:31,598
...l was surprised that he took
such a likin' to me.

135
00:10:31,876 --> 00:10:34,106
Especially when he could've had
any other girl...

136
00:10:34,179 --> 00:10:35,840
...if hed given it half a try.

137
00:10:38,316 --> 00:10:41,945
He said that I was grand, though.
He wasn't interested in me for sex...

138
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,588
...and that comin' from him,
this was a compliment.

139
00:10:44,656 --> 00:10:47,887
He'd never met a 15-year-old girl
who'd behaved like a grownup...

140
00:10:47,959 --> 00:10:49,449
...and wasn't giggly.

141
00:10:49,561 --> 00:10:51,688
He didn't care what anybody else thought.

142
00:10:51,763 --> 00:10:54,323
I looked good to him
and whatever I did was okay.

143
00:10:54,399 --> 00:10:55,957
And if I didn't have a lot to say...

144
00:10:56,034 --> 00:10:58,161
...well that was okay, too.

145
00:11:00,738 --> 00:11:02,399
What a nice place.

146
00:11:04,509 --> 00:11:06,704
Yeah, the tree makes it nice.

147
00:11:07,612 --> 00:11:09,045
And the flowers.

148
00:11:10,748 --> 00:11:12,215
Let's not pick 'em.

149
00:11:13,851 --> 00:11:15,318
They're so nice.

150
00:11:17,355 --> 00:11:18,822
It's your play.

151
00:11:21,726 --> 00:11:24,752
Of course, I had to keep all this a secret
from my dad.

152
00:11:24,929 --> 00:11:27,989
He would've had a fit
since Kit was ten years older than me...

153
00:11:28,066 --> 00:11:30,967
...and came from the wrong side
of the tracks, so-called.

154
00:11:31,035 --> 00:11:34,698
Our time with each other was limited
and each lived for the precious hours...

155
00:11:34,772 --> 00:11:39,505
...when he or she could be with the other,
away from all the cares of the world.

156
00:11:40,411 --> 00:11:42,276
My stomach's growling.

157
00:11:44,782 --> 00:11:47,250
There's an old Fudgesicle. You want it?

158
00:11:48,353 --> 00:11:49,342
No.

159
00:11:50,121 --> 00:11:51,952
Somebody else is gonna get it.

160
00:11:53,024 --> 00:11:54,252
I don't care.

161
00:11:57,528 --> 00:12:00,053
Kids eat that kind of stuff in Korea.

162
00:12:01,899 --> 00:12:04,390
In the stench and slime of the feedlot...

163
00:12:04,469 --> 00:12:06,869
...he'd remember how I'd looked
the night before.

164
00:12:06,938 --> 00:12:08,838
How I ran my hand through his hair...

165
00:12:08,906 --> 00:12:11,875
...and traced the outline of his lips
with my fingertip.

166
00:12:12,143 --> 00:12:16,637
He wanted to die with me, and I dreamed
of being lost forever in his arms.

167
00:12:20,785 --> 00:12:22,946
The whole time,
the only thing I did wrong...

168
00:12:23,021 --> 00:12:25,581
...was throwing out my fish
when he got sick.

169
00:12:25,723 --> 00:12:29,682
Later I got a new one, but this incident
kept on bothering me and I turned to Kit.

170
00:12:30,194 --> 00:12:33,493
Well, he was sick, wasn't he?
Couldn't do much about that.

171
00:12:33,765 --> 00:12:34,925
I guess not.

172
00:12:41,506 --> 00:12:44,236
I didn't mind tellin' Kit
about stuff like this...

173
00:12:44,509 --> 00:12:47,069
...'cause strange things happened
in his life too.

174
00:12:47,145 --> 00:12:49,579
And some of the stuff he did was strange.

175
00:12:49,781 --> 00:12:52,909
For instance, he faked his signature
whenever he used it...

176
00:12:52,984 --> 00:12:56,886
...to keep other people from forgin'
important papers with his name.

177
00:13:00,992 --> 00:13:04,018
And as he lay in bed,
in the middle of the night...

178
00:13:04,162 --> 00:13:08,496
...he always heard a noise like somebody
was holdin' a seashell against his ear.

179
00:13:08,566 --> 00:13:12,195
And sometimes he'd see me comin'
toward him in beautiful white robes...

180
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:14,966
...and I'd put my cold hand on his forehead.

181
00:13:24,449 --> 00:13:26,314
Did it go the way it's supposed to?

182
00:13:28,619 --> 00:13:29,608
Yeah.

183
00:13:31,189 --> 00:13:32,656
Is that all there is to it?

184
00:13:33,391 --> 00:13:34,415
Yeah.

185
00:13:38,863 --> 00:13:40,922
Gosh, what was everybody talkin' about?

186
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,599
Don't ask me.

187
00:13:46,938 --> 00:13:48,769
Well, I'm glad it's over.

188
00:13:49,474 --> 00:13:52,204
For a while I was afraid I might die
before it happened.

189
00:13:52,443 --> 00:13:54,673
Had a wreck or some deal like that.

190
00:13:54,746 --> 00:13:57,374
See where that tree fell in the water?

191
00:13:58,015 --> 00:13:58,913
Yeah.

192
00:13:59,751 --> 00:14:02,276
River must've washed the roots away.

193
00:14:03,454 --> 00:14:05,854
You don't care
about anything I say, though.

194
00:14:07,759 --> 00:14:09,522
-You know what I think?
-What?

195
00:14:09,594 --> 00:14:11,960
We should crunch our hands
with this stone.

196
00:14:12,263 --> 00:14:14,493
That way we'd never forget
what happened today.

197
00:14:14,565 --> 00:14:15,862
But it would hurt.

198
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:18,231
Well, that's the point, stupid.

199
00:14:21,072 --> 00:14:22,869
Don't call me, "stupid."

200
00:14:24,675 --> 00:14:27,303
Okay, but I'm gonna keep it for a souvenir.

201
00:14:30,214 --> 00:14:32,307
Well, maybe one that's lighter.

202
00:14:44,061 --> 00:14:47,030
Kit made a solemn vow
that he would always stand beside me...

203
00:14:47,098 --> 00:14:49,157
...and let nothin' come between us.

204
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:51,929
He wrote this out in writing,
put the paper in a box...

205
00:14:52,003 --> 00:14:56,235
...with some of our little tokens and things,
then sent it off in a balloon he'd found...

206
00:14:56,307 --> 00:14:58,434
...while on the garbage route.

207
00:14:59,043 --> 00:15:02,479
His heart was filled with longin'
as he watched it drift off.

208
00:15:02,547 --> 00:15:03,775
Something must've told him...

209
00:15:03,848 --> 00:15:06,612
...that we'd never live these days
of happiness again...

210
00:15:06,684 --> 00:15:08,379
...that they were gone forever.

211
00:15:19,897 --> 00:15:23,628
Then, sure enough, Dad found out
I'd been runnin' around behind his back.

212
00:15:23,701 --> 00:15:25,794
He was madder than I'd ever seen him.

213
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:29,328
As punishment for deceiving him,
he went and shot my dog.

214
00:15:57,468 --> 00:16:00,733
He made me take extra music lessons
every day after school...

215
00:16:00,938 --> 00:16:03,429
...and wait there till he came
to pick me up.

216
00:16:03,508 --> 00:16:06,375
He said that if the piano
didn't keep me off the streets...

217
00:16:06,444 --> 00:16:08,173
...maybe the clarinet would.

218
00:16:17,221 --> 00:16:18,518
Sure is pretty.

219
00:16:23,461 --> 00:16:25,156
What'd you come out here for?

220
00:16:29,734 --> 00:16:31,998
I wasn't aware there was
any law against it.

221
00:16:42,747 --> 00:16:43,839
You know, Holly...

222
00:16:45,616 --> 00:16:48,346
...well, she means an awful lot to me, sir.

223
00:16:51,122 --> 00:16:52,953
You know, before I met her...

224
00:16:53,824 --> 00:16:56,816
...nobody could ask me
how I was doin' with my girl.

225
00:16:57,261 --> 00:16:59,388
Matter of fact, I didn't really have one.

226
00:16:59,997 --> 00:17:01,430
Is that right?

227
00:17:11,742 --> 00:17:13,767
It okay me leanin' on your Willys here?

228
00:17:22,787 --> 00:17:24,914
I got a lot of respect for her, too, sir.

229
00:17:31,228 --> 00:17:33,560
It's about as good a one
as I know to tell you.

230
00:17:35,366 --> 00:17:36,594
It's not good enough.

231
00:17:38,569 --> 00:17:41,470
What do you think'll happen to her
if she stuck with you, Kit?

232
00:17:41,539 --> 00:17:42,563
A guy like you?

233
00:17:43,407 --> 00:17:44,772
She'd get along okay.

234
00:17:46,177 --> 00:17:47,872
And if she didn't, why...

235
00:17:48,846 --> 00:17:50,609
...she could just take off.

236
00:17:50,715 --> 00:17:52,774
Just take right on off, I wouldn't mind.

237
00:17:54,285 --> 00:17:56,879
I'd always tell people I deserved it.

238
00:18:07,765 --> 00:18:10,063
I don't want you hangin' around anymore.

239
00:18:10,434 --> 00:18:12,334
I don't want to see you again.

240
00:18:13,170 --> 00:18:14,262
Understand?

241
00:18:27,451 --> 00:18:28,645
You're something.

242
00:18:34,992 --> 00:18:36,789
Takes all kinds, sir.

243
00:20:14,325 --> 00:20:15,314
Hi.

244
00:20:16,494 --> 00:20:18,189
What are you doing?

245
00:20:20,131 --> 00:20:21,496
I got a gun here, sir.

246
00:20:22,566 --> 00:20:24,830
Always a good idea to have one around.

247
00:20:26,470 --> 00:20:28,131
What do you think you're doin'?

248
00:20:32,877 --> 00:20:34,208
Go on, get out of here.

249
00:20:36,180 --> 00:20:37,807
I got it all planned.

250
00:20:38,949 --> 00:20:39,779
And...

251
00:20:40,985 --> 00:20:42,680
...Im takin' Holly off with me.

252
00:20:44,789 --> 00:20:45,687
Okay, boy...

253
00:20:46,991 --> 00:20:49,516
...Im turnin' you over to the authorities.

254
00:20:50,728 --> 00:20:51,558
What for?

255
00:20:51,695 --> 00:20:52,821
Comin' on my property...

256
00:20:52,897 --> 00:20:54,159
...with a gun.

257
00:20:57,134 --> 00:20:58,897
No, you're not either.

258
00:20:58,969 --> 00:21:00,459
Yeah? Why not?

259
00:21:01,906 --> 00:21:03,305
'Cause I can't allow it.

260
00:21:06,443 --> 00:21:07,102
Hey!

261
00:21:07,978 --> 00:21:09,206
Hey, wait a minute!

262
00:21:12,716 --> 00:21:14,149
Suppose I shot you?

263
00:21:15,352 --> 00:21:16,614
How'd that be?

264
00:21:19,390 --> 00:21:21,153
Want to hear what it sounds like?

265
00:21:33,003 --> 00:21:34,402
Kit! Kit!

266
00:21:34,471 --> 00:21:35,665
Where are you going?

267
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,270
Wait!

268
00:21:44,715 --> 00:21:45,443
Daddy?

269
00:21:47,618 --> 00:21:48,607
This is Holly.

270
00:21:51,655 --> 00:21:53,520
Are you gonna be okay?

271
00:22:26,023 --> 00:22:27,752
I came in the front.

272
00:22:29,293 --> 00:22:30,817
How bad off is he?

273
00:22:32,663 --> 00:22:34,358
I can look and see.

274
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:37,829
We better call the doctor.

275
00:22:41,138 --> 00:22:44,198
Listen, I'll say how it happened.
Part I saw.

276
00:22:46,076 --> 00:22:47,065
Well...

277
00:22:48,245 --> 00:22:50,076
...l don't think that'd work.

278
00:23:01,225 --> 00:23:03,056
He don't need a doctor.

279
00:23:08,666 --> 00:23:09,928
Are you sure?

280
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,468
If you don't believe me, see for yourself.

281
00:24:05,389 --> 00:24:07,016
I found a toaster.

282
00:24:18,102 --> 00:24:19,501
Don't worry, honey, I'll--

283
00:24:49,199 --> 00:24:52,168
Listen, maybe we ought
to tell somebody about this.

284
00:24:54,571 --> 00:24:56,664
You said that once already.

285
00:24:57,474 --> 00:24:58,771
Too late now.

286
00:24:59,877 --> 00:25:00,866
Why?

287
00:25:02,346 --> 00:25:04,439
They're not going to listen to me.

288
00:25:04,748 --> 00:25:06,682
You either. You kidding?

289
00:25:12,523 --> 00:25:14,787
Suppose the neighbors heard the noise?

290
00:25:16,894 --> 00:25:18,555
Wouldn't be funny.

291
00:25:24,568 --> 00:25:25,592
Listen...

292
00:25:26,904 --> 00:25:28,496
...Ill be back after a while.

293
00:25:34,711 --> 00:25:37,077
You want to call the police, that's fine.

294
00:25:37,181 --> 00:25:38,944
Just won't be so hot for me.

295
00:26:53,423 --> 00:26:56,187
My girl, Holly, and I have decided
to kill ourselves.

296
00:26:56,326 --> 00:26:58,021
Same way I did her dad.

297
00:26:58,996 --> 00:27:00,463
Big decision.

298
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:05,167
The reasons are obvious.

299
00:27:05,235 --> 00:27:07,999
Now, I don't have time
to go into 'em right now.

300
00:27:09,940 --> 00:27:11,999
But, one thing though:

301
00:27:13,177 --> 00:27:15,543
He was provokin' me when I popped him.

302
00:27:16,113 --> 00:27:18,445
That's what it was like, pop!

303
00:27:20,117 --> 00:27:21,709
Now we're sorry.

304
00:27:22,319 --> 00:27:27,018
I mean, nobody's comin' out
of this thing happy, especially not us.

305
00:27:30,093 --> 00:27:32,152
I can't deny we've had fun though.

306
00:27:32,729 --> 00:27:33,787
And...

307
00:27:34,731 --> 00:27:36,824
...that's more than I can say for some.

308
00:27:40,170 --> 00:27:43,799
That's the end of the message.
I ran out of things to say.

309
00:27:46,777 --> 00:27:47,869
Thank you.

310
00:28:41,765 --> 00:28:44,598
My girl, Holly, and I have decided
to kill ourselves.

311
00:28:44,701 --> 00:28:46,601
Same way I did her dad.

312
00:28:47,070 --> 00:28:50,938
Kit left the record playin' over and over
for the district attorney to find.

313
00:28:51,108 --> 00:28:52,973
He was gamblin' for time.

314
00:29:09,493 --> 00:29:13,156
"When Jesus walked into the garden

315
